WEBVTT

00:31.490 --> 00:34.280
What happened?

00:37.520 --> 00:39.880
Something really bad.

00:56.410 --> 00:59.380
Let me use your last card.

01:00.930 --> 01:04.459
I need a chopper.

01:04.459 --> 01:10.670
I have a date to keep.

01:46.570 --> 01:48.289
I'm starting to feel better.

01:48.830 --> 01:50.270
The medicine's working.

01:51.640 --> 01:52.740
That's good.

01:56.590 --> 01:58.770
Why are you wearing that?

02:00.850 --> 02:02.120
Where are you going?

02:04.150 --> 02:07.740
Dr. Kang and Big Boss
are currently missing.

02:08.600 --> 02:11.880
I think Dr. Kang's been kidnapped

02:13.120 --> 02:15.320
and Big Boss, who's unreachable

02:16.470 --> 02:19.070
might be carrying out a solo operation.

02:21.400 --> 02:22.220
Are you...

02:22.220 --> 02:23.910
You said my present was on the way.

02:24.400 --> 02:27.200
Can I open it now?

03:01.470 --> 03:02.730
Don't lose them.

03:04.090 --> 03:06.180
If you lose them, we have to pay for them.

03:09.950 --> 03:14.680
You know you have to come back, right?

03:20.620 --> 03:23.920
We're carrying out an unauthorized black op.

03:24.260 --> 03:27.450
We're going to be dealing with armed gangsters

03:27.450 --> 03:29.350
and we have no backup.

03:29.350 --> 03:31.870
We'll carry out this operation without army uniforms.

03:32.190 --> 03:34.329
We might not all be able to return.

03:34.329 --> 03:36.010
Now's the time to say if you want out.

03:37.320 --> 03:38.700
Does anyone want out?

03:38.700 --> 03:39.720
No, sir!

03:40.770 --> 03:43.430
Good. Vacation's over.

03:44.790 --> 03:48.860
As of now, you're Alpha Team members again.

05:36.100 --> 05:38.659
The deal with North Uruk is done.

05:38.659 --> 05:41.220
They transferred all the money.

05:44.640 --> 05:46.580
Lighten up.

05:49.950 --> 05:54.890
We're in the money...

06:08.050 --> 06:09.410
What should we do with the kids?

06:09.410 --> 06:12.550
You should dump everything that doesn't fit in a suitcase.

06:14.180 --> 06:16.660
Get rid of the children.

06:16.660 --> 06:18.120
Yes, sir.

06:22.930 --> 06:25.180
Go, go, go!

06:37.040 --> 06:37.990
Drop your gun!

06:55.970 --> 06:57.300
What are you doing here?

06:57.300 --> 07:00.070
What were you doing here alone with both of your hands up?

07:01.210 --> 07:02.760
I was scared since I was alone.

07:04.110 --> 07:06.420
But I knew you were here, so I was cheering for you.

07:06.580 --> 07:07.970
Don't be scared.

07:07.970 --> 07:10.400
All the members of Alpha Team are here.

07:12.780 --> 07:15.620
I'll thank you properly when I have more time.

07:17.020 --> 07:18.390
Captain Big Boss

07:18.810 --> 07:20.720
is in charge of this operation.

07:22.790 --> 07:25.890
Piccolo, Harry Potter, take the kids

07:26.370 --> 07:28.090
to a safe place immediately.

07:28.090 --> 07:29.430
Yes, sir.

07:30.060 --> 07:31.780
Wolf and Snoopy,

07:31.780 --> 07:35.659
you'll join me in the operation.

07:35.659 --> 07:36.390
Yes, sir!

07:36.390 --> 07:37.680
Yes, sir!

07:38.790 --> 07:39.620
What?

07:39.810 --> 07:42.590
Who started what operation?

07:42.590 --> 07:44.610
The Republic of Korea Army

07:44.610 --> 07:46.970
Special Warfare Command has started

07:47.470 --> 07:48.760
an unofficial black op...

07:48.760 --> 07:50.420
Excuse me, General Yoon!

07:50.930 --> 07:53.330
How dare you...

07:53.990 --> 07:55.550
Geeze.

07:56.100 --> 07:57.780
The US Army promised that they'd rescue

07:57.780 --> 08:00.370
the hostage in 24 hours.

08:00.370 --> 08:01.880
The Korean Army
went to

08:01.880 --> 08:03.660
rescue a Korean citizen.

08:03.660 --> 08:05.500
There's nothing for you not to understand.

08:05.500 --> 08:08.880
This isn't just a simple civilian kidnapping case.

08:09.320 --> 08:12.810
What if we ruin the CIA operation?

08:12.810 --> 08:14.850
Who's going to be responsible for that?

08:14.850 --> 08:17.620
I understand your situation as a diplomatic...

08:17.620 --> 08:19.900
Don't cut me off.

08:19.900 --> 08:23.090
This is a matter of national security

08:23.090 --> 08:26.230
that has to be dealt with politically and diplomatically.

08:26.270 --> 08:29.660
Why don't you let the US Army rescue the hostage

08:29.660 --> 08:33.650
and we concentrate on keeping the secrets and controlling the media.

08:33.650 --> 08:36.750
Hey. Politician!

08:40.530 --> 08:42.530
What did you say?

08:43.990 --> 08:45.660
I hope I didn't hear you right.

08:46.510 --> 08:49.380
If you didn't hear me right, I'll tell you again.

08:50.530 --> 08:52.760
For you people, national security is just politics

08:53.330 --> 08:55.330
that you discuss in closed rooms

08:55.330 --> 08:57.810
and talk about in front of cameras.

08:58.550 --> 09:00.130
For my men,

09:00.170 --> 09:02.810
it's their country that they protect while giving up their youth

09:02.810 --> 09:06.310
and risking their lives.

09:06.930 --> 09:09.820
They answer when their nation calls

09:10.490 --> 09:12.610
while knowing that no one will remember

09:12.610 --> 09:15.490
their names or restore their honor.

09:15.800 --> 09:18.720
Because they believe that the citizens' lives

09:18.720 --> 09:20.280
are a matter of national security.

09:23.120 --> 09:23.800
I'll take full responsibility

09:23.800 --> 09:26.540
as their commander.

09:26.940 --> 09:30.260
Why don't you wear a fancy tie

09:30.260 --> 09:33.130
and have a press conference?

09:34.760 --> 09:36.300
Geeze.

09:37.250 --> 09:38.820
That means that you're willing

09:39.940 --> 09:43.240
to resign from your position?

09:44.910 --> 09:48.440
For an honorable reason. Anytime.

09:57.510 --> 10:00.860
Ye Hwa prepared this for you. It'll help you recuperate.

10:01.830 --> 10:03.090
Drink up!

10:09.320 --> 10:11.770
So many people worried me.

10:17.940 --> 10:20.800
I hate to do this

10:20.800 --> 10:22.470
to someone who almost died...

10:24.230 --> 10:26.420
But what's happening to Dr. Kang?

10:26.420 --> 10:28.140
Haven’t you heard anything from Dr. Seo?

10:28.140 --> 10:30.390
Has Dr. Kang been kidnapped?

10:30.390 --> 10:33.330
Did the Captain and his team

10:33.690 --> 10:35.110
go to rescue Dr. Kang?

10:36.060 --> 10:37.210
Don't worry.

10:38.520 --> 10:39.510
They'll rescue her. Whatever it takes.

10:41.520 --> 10:42.690
Whatever it takes?

10:44.230 --> 10:46.220
It's better for you not to know.

11:03.910 --> 11:06.010
Time's up.

11:06.660 --> 11:09.730
Let's see if your boyfriend

11:09.730 --> 11:10.950
kept his promise.

11:11.220 --> 11:12.810
Let's get you dressed up.

11:13.540 --> 11:14.660
Let's go.

11:28.860 --> 11:31.530
I think they're still in the building.

11:33.610 --> 11:34.590
Hurry up! Here we go!

11:50.000 --> 11:52.370
I have secured your retreat route like you asked.

11:52.370 --> 11:53.920
The helicopter will arrive on time.

11:53.920 --> 11:56.690
I only asked for a retreat route

11:56.690 --> 11:59.080
but kindly a guide came with it.

12:01.470 --> 12:03.150
I kept my word.

12:03.150 --> 12:04.290
So

12:04.290 --> 12:05.580
should you.

12:06.520 --> 12:09.340
Let the hostage go.

12:22.090 --> 12:23.420
Did you hit her?

12:24.680 --> 12:27.320
Everyone! Lock on the target!

12:27.710 --> 12:29.180
This is Wild Wolf.

12:29.490 --> 12:30.980
I have a lock on the target.

12:37.570 --> 12:38.710
Abort! Abort!

12:38.710 --> 12:40.050
Everyone! Hold your fire!

12:42.570 --> 12:43.690
Snoopy.

12:44.920 --> 12:48.370
Do you recognize the explosives wrapped around the hostage's body?

12:48.370 --> 12:49.320
It looks like

12:49.320 --> 12:51.610
a regular PVC pipe type bomb vest,

12:51.840 --> 12:52.770
but the detonator in his hand is tension triggered.

12:52.770 --> 12:54.620
If he releases it, it'll go off.

12:54.620 --> 12:56.200
What if we just blow up his wrist?

12:56.200 --> 12:57.500
Calm down.

12:57.500 --> 13:00.020
If we shoot him, the vest will go off.

13:00.370 --> 13:01.460
Is there any other way?

13:01.460 --> 13:02.780
I'm coming over.

13:24.580 --> 13:26.880
Quit playing around and let the helicopter land.

13:26.880 --> 13:28.720
Let her go first.

13:28.720 --> 13:30.350
Or else

13:30.350 --> 13:32.410
we do not land.

13:32.410 --> 13:34.910
I have to be in a safe area first.

13:34.910 --> 13:36.590
Or else,

13:42.500 --> 13:44.110
she will die.

13:47.870 --> 13:49.730
There'll be a wireless radio connected to the detonator.

13:49.970 --> 13:50.990
Can you stall him?

13:52.890 --> 13:55.590
What are they saying, doctor?

13:56.630 --> 13:58.140
About the weather.

13:58.140 --> 14:00.050
Such a beautiful day, they said.

14:00.530 --> 14:01.620
Do you want to die?

14:04.360 --> 14:05.680
Are you crazy?

14:06.130 --> 14:08.700
I guess you can say that.

14:09.200 --> 14:10.700
So...

14:10.700 --> 14:12.420
Don't scare her.

14:12.420 --> 14:13.720
Don't touch her.

14:13.890 --> 14:15.500
Don't talk to her.

14:16.360 --> 14:18.590
It's only me

14:18.590 --> 14:20.320
you should deal with.

14:22.120 --> 14:23.480
Take me instead.

14:25.120 --> 14:26.440
No, thank you.

14:30.500 --> 14:33.760
It's much more fun to travel with a beautiful lady.

14:34.840 --> 14:36.170
It's a seam on her left shoulder.

14:36.920 --> 14:39.080
There's a dim green light on her right shoulder.

14:39.700 --> 14:40.700
I'm sure that's it.

14:53.040 --> 14:54.150
I'm sorry I'm late.

14:56.830 --> 15:00.240
Don't move and stay still.

15:02.170 --> 15:03.700
You trust me, don't you?

15:06.350 --> 15:08.180
Don't move a muscle.

15:12.550 --> 15:13.640
What are you doing?

15:14.670 --> 15:16.180
Taking my shot.

16:00.210 --> 16:01.180
How long will it take?

16:01.510 --> 16:02.460
One minute will suffice.

16:02.610 --> 16:04.020
I can disarm it in one minute.

16:04.490 --> 16:05.570
Please don't move.

16:06.140 --> 16:09.820
I'm not moving. I'm trying not to move.

16:09.820 --> 16:12.220
Look at me. Look into my eyes.

16:15.900 --> 16:19.630
Do you remember when I fooled you about the mines?

16:20.320 --> 16:23.430
You told me to bring an expert.

16:24.170 --> 16:25.080
I've been in the army for 15 years,

16:25.080 --> 16:26.590
including the Army Academy,

16:27.340 --> 16:29.580
and I've never seen an explosive that Sergeant Choi couldn't disarm.

16:30.770 --> 16:32.660
He's the best in the army.

16:34.880 --> 16:36.110
You don't have to worry.

16:37.310 --> 16:39.300
I won't let you die.

16:41.390 --> 16:44.890
But still, we only have 30 seconds.

16:45.790 --> 16:47.430
Why don't you two run?

16:48.850 --> 16:50.690
We can do lots of things in 30 seconds.

16:54.380 --> 16:56.570
Okay. I'm taking it off.

16:56.570 --> 16:57.420
See?

17:00.120 --> 17:01.500
I've removed the vest from her,

17:01.500 --> 17:02.950
but I couldn't stop the timer.

17:02.950 --> 17:04.030
It'll still go off.

17:04.520 --> 17:05.740
Duck!

17:15.790 --> 17:17.170
Big Boss. Nine o'clock!

17:47.110 --> 17:48.460
Forget this.

18:38.360 --> 18:40.440
Call from Korea, Captain

18:41.350 --> 18:42.630
Sir!

18:43.430 --> 18:47.790
Captain Yoo Shi Jin. I'm coming in. The operation is complete.

18:49.030 --> 18:53.040
The target was killed and the hostage is safe.

18:55.560 --> 18:57.770
I'll surrender my weapons and wait in the barracks.

18:58.770 --> 19:02.500
I'm willing to accept any punishment.

19:03.120 --> 19:05.050
You did a great job.

19:05.350 --> 19:08.240
You're not going to be rewarded for what you did,

19:08.240 --> 19:10.260
but you won't be punished either.

19:10.260 --> 19:11.940
That's your reward.

19:11.940 --> 19:12.980
General Yoon!

19:12.980 --> 19:16.010
Don't worry about a thing and get some rest.

19:17.030 --> 19:20.400
That's all. I can't believe this.

19:23.090 --> 19:25.430
Can I write down that this operation

19:25.430 --> 19:27.760
was done under your direct order?

19:28.230 --> 19:30.060
Please do.

19:32.630 --> 19:35.080
This will stir up trouble.

19:35.080 --> 19:37.360
At least we won't have to worry about whom to blame.

19:39.050 --> 19:40.920
I've already made a report to the Blue House.

19:40.920 --> 19:43.490
The level of punishment we should impose...

19:46.530 --> 19:47.680
Mr. President is coming.

19:47.680 --> 19:48.450
Now?

19:48.450 --> 19:50.250
- Yes.
- Here?

19:55.440 --> 19:57.210
I read your report on my way here.

19:57.210 --> 19:58.390
Have a seat.

20:01.130 --> 20:02.780
I heard that the hostage is safe.

20:03.200 --> 20:06.600
Yes, but the CIA is

20:06.640 --> 20:08.410
strongly appealing

20:08.410 --> 20:10.730
to us about our solo operation.

20:11.550 --> 20:14.570
It'll put us in a diplomatically awkward position.

20:14.570 --> 20:17.000
It'll disadvantage us when making trade negotiations.

20:17.800 --> 20:20.640
Before they blame the Korean government,

20:20.640 --> 20:22.540
we should punish the commander

20:22.540 --> 20:25.080
in charge of this operation.

20:27.090 --> 20:28.200
Should we?

20:30.950 --> 20:34.310
I'm Lieutenant General Yoon Gil Jun.

20:35.110 --> 20:36.440
I feel the same way.

20:37.510 --> 20:40.820
I'll take full responsibility.

20:40.820 --> 20:42.430
I don't agree.

20:44.040 --> 20:46.350
Your hostage rescue operation was successful.

20:46.350 --> 20:49.100
You didn't do anything wrong.

20:50.380 --> 20:52.100
The hostage is safe.

20:52.100 --> 20:53.920
We have a political and diplomatic issue.

20:54.880 --> 20:57.110
That's something I should take care of.

20:57.620 --> 21:00.350
I'll take full responsibility.

21:01.060 --> 21:02.970
But Mr. President!

21:02.970 --> 21:04.640
Make a list of any possible problems

21:04.640 --> 21:05.940
that we might encounter

21:05.940 --> 21:07.180
diplomatically.

21:13.580 --> 21:16.690
Thank you for rescuing a citizen of Korea.

21:18.180 --> 21:23.400
I'm glad no one got hurt while carrying out the operation.

23:10.940 --> 23:13.040
I've never seen a gunshot wound before.

23:13.850 --> 23:16.720
We're out in a bigger world and experiencing many things.

23:17.370 --> 23:19.360
You need stitches.

23:19.360 --> 23:22.260
Okay, bite this first.

23:22.260 --> 23:23.610
Go get some vodka.

23:23.660 --> 23:26.390
Your country will remember you forever.

23:27.470 --> 23:29.060
What?

23:29.790 --> 23:31.860
This is how to treat a gunshot wound.

23:31.860 --> 23:33.070
Haven't you seen it in movies?

23:33.070 --> 23:34.250
In horror films,

23:34.250 --> 23:35.230
chatty doctors like you

23:35.230 --> 23:36.680
always die first.

23:37.170 --> 23:38.270
Bite this pen.

23:44.680 --> 23:46.050
Calm down.

23:47.890 --> 23:49.020
We were worried about you.

23:49.980 --> 23:51.570
I don't know what to say.

23:51.570 --> 23:52.470
Put this in her mouth.

23:52.470 --> 23:53.750
Hey!

23:57.700 --> 24:03.580
One, two, three, four!

24:03.580 --> 24:06.450
One, two, three, four!

24:06.450 --> 24:09.670
One, two, three, four! One, two, three, four!

24:09.670 --> 24:11.320
Singing while running.

24:11.320 --> 24:13.600
The song is "Cool Guy."

24:13.600 --> 24:15.180
-There are
-There are

24:15.180 --> 24:16.570
-lots of
-lots of

24:16.570 --> 24:20.380
cool guys.

24:27.460 --> 24:29.720
-Sergeant Seo!
-Handsome!

24:30.250 --> 24:31.840
Can I talk to you for a minute?

24:37.250 --> 24:40.120
I've tried to be understanding

24:40.120 --> 24:41.860
as a sophisticated and intelligent man,

24:42.490 --> 24:43.670
but why do they do something

24:43.670 --> 24:45.090
as vulgar as this?

24:45.090 --> 24:46.630
I can't stand it.

24:53.880 --> 24:58.450
Sergeant Seo! Sergeant Seo!

25:24.390 --> 25:26.390
How's your wound?

25:28.280 --> 25:30.560
I couldn't ask you with so much going on yesterday.

25:30.830 --> 25:31.940
But is Fatima okay?

25:32.800 --> 25:37.020
She's okay. She's being treated at headquarters.

25:38.400 --> 25:40.290
She'll recover pretty quickly.

25:41.680 --> 25:42.940
Really?

25:43.430 --> 25:45.190
What do you mean?

25:45.190 --> 25:48.040
I have a feeling that
you lie to me quite often.

25:51.000 --> 25:54.130
You said those kids from the ghost town were safe.

25:55.100 --> 25:58.110
But I saw them locked up there.

26:01.710 --> 26:03.520
I'm sorry that I lied to you.

26:05.370 --> 26:07.390
I didn't want you to worry.

26:08.920 --> 26:11.860
How many more lies
have you told me so far

26:12.840 --> 26:14.880
to prevent me from worrying?

26:18.790 --> 26:20.600
How did you get hurt?

26:21.730 --> 26:23.240
While shoveling in my regiment.

26:23.240 --> 26:25.640
Are you okay? Did anyone get hurt?

26:26.220 --> 26:27.600
It was a simple traffic accident.

26:28.000 --> 26:29.590
You must've been shocked. Are you okay?

26:29.590 --> 26:31.530
Can I ask you what it's about?

26:32.240 --> 26:34.340
I need to be at headquarters.

26:35.790 --> 26:41.580
I haven't told you any lies other than that.

26:44.430 --> 26:45.950
You're lying.

26:51.040 --> 26:53.570
What's your excuse behind that lie you just told?

26:56.570 --> 26:58.420
Now I understand.

26:59.420 --> 27:01.240
The lies that you've told me

27:02.300 --> 27:04.240
aren't the kind of lies I can tell you to come clean with

27:04.240 --> 27:07.720
and threaten to break up with you if you don't.

27:09.210 --> 27:11.000
Behind your lies,

27:11.640 --> 27:13.480
someone's life is at stake

27:14.230 --> 27:16.240
and politics and diplomacy are involved

27:16.240 --> 27:18.200
and countries react.

27:19.210 --> 27:21.110
You made jokes

27:22.390 --> 27:26.300
to hide the things that you couldn't tell me.

27:27.840 --> 27:30.470
You'll keep making silly jokes

27:30.520 --> 27:32.800
to hide the things that you can't tell me.

27:32.800 --> 27:34.130
And I won't be able to trust you.

27:34.880 --> 27:37.150
And eventually, there'll be nothing

27:37.950 --> 27:40.140
to talk about between us.

27:44.130 --> 27:47.570
How angry I was in the morning because of

27:47.570 --> 27:50.580
this jerk who parked like a drunken idiot.

27:50.580 --> 27:52.210
I can't decide whether I should eat kimchi stew

27:52.210 --> 27:54.300
or bean paste stew for lunch.

27:56.290 --> 27:59.120
I'm not happy because my package didn't show up.

27:59.120 --> 28:00.890
I just want to talk to you

28:00.890 --> 28:02.500
about those small things.

28:05.820 --> 28:07.030
Go ahead.

28:09.490 --> 28:11.570
For me, every single thing you say is important.

28:14.810 --> 28:16.100
I know.

28:18.030 --> 28:20.600
I trust you,

28:20.600 --> 28:21.900
but...

28:24.980 --> 28:27.850
I can't tell those things to someone

28:29.560 --> 28:31.550
who stoped bullets with his own body.

28:40.750 --> 28:42.480
Do you want to break up with me?

28:50.270 --> 28:56.770
I'm not sure if you're a man I can handle.

29:05.730 --> 29:07.060
Big Boss!

29:07.580 --> 29:09.170
He's smart,

29:09.220 --> 29:11.790
funny,

29:11.790 --> 29:13.390
and mysterious.

29:14.620 --> 29:16.230
But

29:16.230 --> 29:18.460
he has a lot of secrets.

29:22.220 --> 29:24.670
He'll disappear from time to time.

29:25.030 --> 29:26.960
Be hard to contact.

29:27.920 --> 29:29.780
And then, one day...

29:35.490 --> 29:38.100
He'll never come back.

29:54.420 --> 29:56.980
Thanks for your gift, Big Boss.

29:57.420 --> 29:58.790
Thanks to you,

29:58.790 --> 30:03.600
over 200 people have to write thousands of pages of reports again.

30:05.380 --> 30:08.300
Now I realize what I just did.

30:08.950 --> 30:10.050
My apology.

30:10.090 --> 30:13.180
It's a good day when a failed op results

30:13.180 --> 30:15.070
only in paperwork instead of our lives lost.

30:15.070 --> 30:17.350
You don't have to apologize to anyone.

30:18.090 --> 30:20.560
Thanks for not reporting on that day.

30:20.560 --> 30:22.480
Because of you,

30:22.860 --> 30:26.230
I was able to avoid
struggles in my own troops.

30:26.230 --> 30:29.000
No, I reported you.

30:30.280 --> 30:32.200
Just a little bit late.

30:35.900 --> 30:41.420
Seems very lonely with no honor and no country to serve.

30:44.870 --> 30:46.900
See you again.

30:48.370 --> 30:49.690
Big Boss!

30:53.080 --> 30:55.480
Even if I never see you again,

30:55.480 --> 30:57.110
you stay alive.

30:57.580 --> 30:59.030
Take care.

31:09.020 --> 31:12.380
The patients will leave on Wednesday, two days before the medical services team.

31:12.420 --> 31:14.380
And we'll leave on Friday night.

31:14.380 --> 31:17.430
Therefore, the Haeseong Hospital medical team

31:17.470 --> 31:20.200
will be disbanded officially at midnight on Thursday.

31:20.840 --> 31:23.760
Wow, we're really going home.

31:23.760 --> 31:24.700
Tell me honestly.

31:24.700 --> 31:26.050
Were we fired or disbanded?

31:26.050 --> 31:27.520
Why? Do you feel sad?

31:27.810 --> 31:29.650
I thought you were dying to go home.

31:29.650 --> 31:32.330
I don't know. I'm definitely not jumping for joy.

31:32.720 --> 31:33.690
Is it just me?

31:34.450 --> 31:38.330
Me too. I feel a little gloomy.

31:39.450 --> 31:41.340
Me too.

31:45.110 --> 31:46.570
Shall we start?

31:47.050 --> 31:49.370
These are our last rounds in Uruk.

32:01.650 --> 32:03.520
I guess you sure are a soldier.

32:03.970 --> 32:05.210
You're recovering so fast.

32:05.390 --> 32:06.870
I recover fast

32:06.870 --> 32:07.830
because I'm young.

32:09.450 --> 32:11.200
I guess you're all better.

32:11.520 --> 32:14.150
You can be discharged after resting for two more days.

32:17.160 --> 32:18.900
Okay. Why don't you stay right there?

32:19.400 --> 32:21.250
It's my turn.

32:22.100 --> 32:23.200
What are you doing?

32:23.870 --> 32:24.920
Are you taking your medicine?

32:25.770 --> 32:27.790
Change the dressing often so you won't get infected.

32:27.790 --> 32:29.590
You can start showering again in two days.

32:30.800 --> 32:32.110
You can go now.

32:37.820 --> 32:41.440
He can eat porridge starting tomorrow and keep giving him antibiotics.

32:42.970 --> 32:44.730
You're over the hump.

32:45.390 --> 32:48.050
Because of you, a lot of people might have died.

32:48.840 --> 32:50.470
You're going to be transferred to Korea.

32:50.470 --> 32:53.290
I want you to be severely punished.

32:54.100 --> 32:57.810
Diamonds. My diamonds.

32:58.550 --> 33:00.750
The US Army took the diamonds.

33:00.750 --> 33:02.040
You'll never find them.

33:03.240 --> 33:04.840
I hope you're happy.

33:14.980 --> 33:16.410
Is everything okay?

33:16.980 --> 33:20.580
You're the healthiest of all the patients who are going home.

33:21.440 --> 33:23.740
It'll be cold in Korea, right?

33:25.110 --> 33:26.660
I don't like cold weather.

33:27.220 --> 33:31.890
Dr. Kang. Dr. Kang. You have a fax.

33:32.610 --> 33:34.660
It's about Dr. Lee Chi Hoon.

33:34.660 --> 33:36.130
I think his results came in.

33:36.130 --> 33:40.410
Well...Can I deliver that to him?

33:47.990 --> 33:50.870
You're not supposed to be here.

33:50.870 --> 33:52.310
We're all going to Korea.

33:52.750 --> 33:54.210
All the doctors and patients.

33:55.580 --> 33:57.050
You must be happy that you don't have to see me.

34:04.530 --> 34:05.600
I'm not infected.

34:07.680 --> 34:08.530
I'm not infected.

34:08.530 --> 34:09.389
I'm not dying.

34:10.210 --> 34:11.449
Are you happy because you won't die?

34:20.889 --> 34:22.290
Me too.

34:24.389 --> 34:26.940
I'm happy because you're not going to die.

34:32.210 --> 34:32.969
Thank you.

34:32.969 --> 34:35.190
Don't thank me or say sorry to me.

34:35.710 --> 34:36.739
I won't say those things to you.

35:03.320 --> 35:04.450
Oh my!

35:07.400 --> 35:08.590
When did you get here?

35:09.590 --> 35:11.050
Did you walk all the way here?

35:13.680 --> 35:15.670
You're all better.

35:16.270 --> 35:19.130
I'm not sick. I'm all better now.

35:19.130 --> 35:21.010
Can you wait here?

35:21.350 --> 35:22.320
I have something for you.

35:25.930 --> 35:28.990
Wear them when you get bigger. This is my present to you.

35:28.990 --> 35:31.360
If you need money, you can sell them.

35:32.420 --> 35:35.000
There aren't even 50 pairs of these shoes in the entire world.

35:35.000 --> 35:37.780
Not this. Give me a goat.

35:37.780 --> 35:40.780
I know. I'm going to miss you too.

35:40.780 --> 35:43.750
By the way, Blacky is where you live.

35:43.750 --> 35:44.960
Then what's your real name?

35:44.960 --> 35:46.750
Give me a goat.

35:46.750 --> 35:48.370
Not this. A goat.

35:48.420 --> 35:50.110
I want to have a goat.

35:50.510 --> 35:54.650
Right. I guess that's your name.

35:54.650 --> 35:57.030
Yes, goat!

35:57.030 --> 35:59.400
Buy me a goat.

35:59.400 --> 36:01.440
I want to have a goat.

36:01.440 --> 36:03.330
Yes. I know how you feel.

36:03.330 --> 36:05.700
I'm glad that I got to know you.

36:08.240 --> 36:09.820
I'm going to miss you a lot.

36:13.430 --> 36:15.650
Don't think that you owe me anything.

36:17.760 --> 36:20.450
Have a good life, okay?

36:44.720 --> 36:46.560
Do you want to break up with me?

37:10.170 --> 37:11.400
Onto the next one, boys! Let's go!

37:11.400 --> 37:14.600
Captain. Look over there.

37:18.350 --> 37:22.360
Pickle. One, two, three!

38:35.630 --> 38:40.010
I want you to forget this as well.

39:23.060 --> 39:25.480
Would you like to have coffee with me?

39:28.700 --> 39:30.630
Can you prepare some coffee for us?

39:31.330 --> 39:33.280
I'll be at the chapel.

40:32.780 --> 40:36.250
I was checking the patients before you came.

40:39.640 --> 40:42.350
I was glad to see Lieutenant Yoon recovering fast.

40:43.680 --> 40:45.290
I was going to put my hair back, but I couldn’t find an elastic.

40:45.290 --> 40:50.300
I checked everywhere, but I couldn't find one.

40:52.240 --> 40:54.620
Elastics are disposable.

41:02.580 --> 41:07.740
I'm even going to tell you about small things like this.

41:09.880 --> 41:12.100
I've decided to embrace who you are.

41:13.180 --> 41:18.050
I want you to embrace the fact that I'm a chatterbox.

41:20.820 --> 41:24.150
I want you to promise one thing.

41:27.580 --> 41:29.820
Let me have the right to worry about you.

41:32.070 --> 41:35.170
I can't be worried and anxious

41:35.170 --> 41:37.500
whenever I can't see you face to face.

41:38.420 --> 41:39.710
So

41:41.360 --> 41:43.880
when you have to do something dangerous,

41:43.880 --> 41:45.330
let me know.

41:46.490 --> 41:49.340
If you say you're going to a department store,

41:49.340 --> 41:53.060
I'll consider it a secret operation.

41:53.060 --> 41:54.290
I’ll understand.

41:56.070 --> 42:00.190
At least when you're fighting to stay alive,

42:00.190 --> 42:02.290
I don't want to be laughing with my friends.

42:10.670 --> 42:14.280
Let me ask you one last question.

42:17.470 --> 42:19.300
Me or your country?

42:21.500 --> 42:22.860
You'd better answer it right.

42:22.860 --> 42:24.370
I'm not going to ask you again.

42:26.730 --> 42:28.070
For now, Kang Mo Yeon.

42:29.080 --> 42:30.310
For now?

42:30.920 --> 42:33.140
You said you wouldn't ask me again.

42:33.140 --> 42:34.360
That was before you said

42:34.360 --> 42:36.170
"For now, Kang Mo Yeon."

42:36.170 --> 42:37.760
What if I ask you again?

42:37.760 --> 42:38.930
Still Kang Mo Yeon.

42:40.520 --> 42:41.400
Really?

42:43.640 --> 42:45.080
What about your country?

42:46.250 --> 42:48.450
My country won’t get jealous.

42:48.450 --> 42:49.670
It just trusts me.

42:51.310 --> 42:53.020
Geeze. What am I doing?

42:53.440 --> 42:55.090
How did I end up

42:55.090 --> 42:56.590
with a guy like him?

43:08.180 --> 43:10.790
The thing you're worried about will never happen.

43:12.840 --> 43:14.520
I promise.

43:18.710 --> 43:20.640
I don't know.

43:24.110 --> 43:25.460
How pretty!

43:25.730 --> 43:28.080
I know that.

43:45.900 --> 43:47.090
I'm okay now.

43:47.790 --> 43:51.400
My fever's gone and I'm ridiculously hungry.

43:52.940 --> 43:54.590
I want to have samgyetang.

43:55.270 --> 43:56.320
Samgyetang?

43:56.320 --> 43:57.330
And samgyeobsal.

43:58.300 --> 43:59.520
When we get back to Korea.

44:00.290 --> 44:01.830
Soju and beer.

44:02.460 --> 44:04.940
To see you craving alcohol, you're all better.

44:05.350 --> 44:08.950
You know what? All my favorite things start with "S."

44:09.600 --> 44:12.180
Samgyetang, samgyeobsal,

44:12.510 --> 44:15.020
soju and beer, and Seo Dae Young.

44:16.770 --> 44:20.000
That's strange. Wait! "Strange" also starts with "S."

44:20.420 --> 44:21.720
Swindler!

44:39.530 --> 44:40.570
So in love with you.

44:48.550 --> 44:49.840
Geeze!

44:49.840 --> 44:51.570
Sir,

44:51.570 --> 44:55.010
you put a bottle cap inside the chicken.

44:55.010 --> 44:56.830
I thought it was a jujube.

44:56.830 --> 44:58.450
It isn't edible.

44:59.600 --> 45:00.270
Even after it's cooked?

45:00.270 --> 45:01.090
What?

45:01.090 --> 45:02.020
Put these in as well.

45:02.020 --> 45:03.650
These taste good when they're cooked.

45:03.650 --> 45:04.600
They sure do.

45:04.600 --> 45:05.730
I guess you know your stuff.

45:06.060 --> 45:07.270
Please.

45:07.600 --> 45:09.700
Can you two just leave me alone?

45:09.700 --> 45:12.310
We want to contribute.

45:12.310 --> 45:13.190
Can we?

45:13.190 --> 45:15.270
I can put this in and start cooking, right?

45:15.270 --> 45:16.320
Sure.

45:16.320 --> 45:17.590
Salt. Salt.

45:17.590 --> 45:20.720
Good. Good.

45:28.740 --> 45:31.200
I'm so impressed.

45:31.610 --> 45:33.180
You look good in an apron.

45:34.110 --> 45:37.780
Don't I look like good husband material?

45:37.780 --> 45:39.190
You two went through a lot

45:39.190 --> 45:41.200
and we prepared this so that you can get some energy.

45:41.480 --> 45:42.840
This is really good.

45:42.840 --> 45:45.690
It's perfect.

45:45.690 --> 45:48.240
Private Kim is a good cook.

45:48.240 --> 45:51.520
Right? I think I'll miss his dishes even when I go back to Korea.

45:51.520 --> 45:53.090
When I went to med school, I ate

45:53.090 --> 45:55.330
samgyetang a lot in front of the school.

45:55.600 --> 45:56.750
I know you did.

45:56.750 --> 45:59.350
I saw you and Min Yoon Gi eat there together.

45:59.350 --> 46:00.860
We didn't go there together.

46:00.860 --> 46:02.040
He just followed me there

46:02.040 --> 46:03.420
saying that he wanted to talk to me.

46:03.760 --> 46:05.970
If you still think that
I came between you two...

46:05.970 --> 46:07.150
You came between us.

46:07.150 --> 46:08.550
What did he want to tell you?

46:08.990 --> 46:10.670
He said there was nothing between you two.

46:10.670 --> 46:11.540
Did he say that?

46:11.540 --> 46:12.690
There was nothing between us?

46:12.690 --> 46:15.110
Yes, he said you two were doing group study.

46:15.160 --> 46:16.400
Group study?

46:17.080 --> 46:18.060
We weren't only studying.

46:18.060 --> 46:19.190
There was something between us

46:19.190 --> 46:19.890
starting in April.

46:19.890 --> 46:22.550
But he asked me out in March right after the semester started.

46:22.550 --> 46:25.030
I meant April the year before.

46:25.030 --> 46:26.420
I guess you had a secret crush on him.

46:26.420 --> 46:27.810
He had feelings for me too.

46:36.240 --> 46:37.560
The reason why they hated each other

46:37.560 --> 46:39.170
was because of this guy called Yoon Gi.

46:39.170 --> 46:40.530
I'm dying to meet this guy named Yoon Gi.

46:40.530 --> 46:41.820
It seems that I couldn’t fall asleep.

46:42.180 --> 46:42.950
It's not what you think.

46:42.950 --> 46:44.120
It's not what you think at all.

46:44.120 --> 46:46.760
You two went berserk over a photo.

46:46.760 --> 46:49.370
I didn't know they had a crush on another guy.

46:49.370 --> 46:50.840
I'm so furious.

46:50.840 --> 46:53.220
I don't know who this lucky guy is

46:53.220 --> 46:54.840
but I want to kill him.

46:58.310 --> 46:59.770
I guess he's a doctor.

47:00.650 --> 47:02.800
Carry out forcible combat plans after making sure the location.

47:07.980 --> 47:10.330
I don't know if I can keep my cool when I see him.

47:11.450 --> 47:12.570
A gun is too easy

47:12.570 --> 47:13.990
and a bomb is too messy.

47:20.160 --> 47:22.730
I guess you and I both put our feet in our mouths.

47:22.730 --> 47:24.810
Who brought up the story about medical school?

47:24.810 --> 47:25.710
You shouldn't have

47:25.710 --> 47:26.920
connected it to Min Yoon Gi.

47:26.920 --> 47:28.830
That's not important at the moment.

47:29.280 --> 47:31.160
How are we going to fix this?

47:32.580 --> 47:33.990
How could we be so stupid

47:33.990 --> 47:35.540
and careless?

47:35.540 --> 47:36.870
Don't worry about me.

47:37.650 --> 47:39.020
Worry about yourself.

47:40.020 --> 47:41.010
Why?

47:41.010 --> 47:43.300
I can pretend that I'm still really sick.

47:43.980 --> 47:47.150
I almost die. He'll forgive me.

47:47.700 --> 47:48.850
I'm so jealous.

47:58.970 --> 48:01.250
It's okay. I have a fever.

48:01.820 --> 48:02.890
Ouch.

48:03.490 --> 48:06.040
Don't worry about me. I'm okay.

48:06.040 --> 48:07.250
I know. You look fine.

48:08.350 --> 48:12.460
I guess you have good memories of Yoon Gi. You're glowing.

48:14.170 --> 48:15.270
Okay, this isn't working.

48:16.030 --> 48:18.210
I have something to discuss with you.

48:20.660 --> 48:21.590
With me?

48:23.180 --> 48:26.050
You have a thing with Yoon Gi but you want to discuss something with me?

48:26.880 --> 48:27.600
No?

48:27.600 --> 48:28.630
Did you think I'd say yes?

48:29.040 --> 48:30.270
Okay.

48:30.270 --> 48:31.050
Speaking of that,

48:31.050 --> 48:32.940
I'm going to call Yoon Gi.

48:34.440 --> 48:35.810
Go ahead and call him. See what happens.

48:35.810 --> 48:37.470
I'm going to call him.

48:45.710 --> 48:47.200
Listen to me carefully.

48:48.180 --> 48:49.500
What is it?

48:49.500 --> 48:52.930
At the moment, I like Yoo Shi Jin the most

48:52.930 --> 48:54.990
of all the existing men on Earth.

48:55.940 --> 48:58.420
I destroyed three cars with him

48:58.470 --> 49:00.100
and was almost drowned with him,

49:00.100 --> 49:02.200
beat an epidemic with him,

49:02.200 --> 49:04.410
and got a gunshot wound because of him.

49:05.170 --> 49:07.850
Despite all those things,

49:07.850 --> 49:09.900
I just can't stop liking him.

49:10.690 --> 49:11.660
Why?

49:12.270 --> 49:15.550
Because he hasn't been coward.

49:15.550 --> 49:17.900
He has kept his honor at all times

49:17.900 --> 49:20.610
and is still amazingly good-looking.

49:22.340 --> 49:23.240
Do you have a problem?

49:25.290 --> 49:26.250
No.

49:27.390 --> 49:30.900
I have something to discuss with you. Do want to hear it or not?

49:34.650 --> 49:37.260
I've wanted to hear it
from the moment I was born.

49:40.480 --> 49:42.650
I'm going to visit Fatima tomorrow

49:42.650 --> 49:44.870
and I was wondering if Daniel and Ye Hwa

49:44.870 --> 49:47.310
would be willing to become her guardians.

49:47.630 --> 49:51.630
But they don't stay in one place and come and go as they please.

49:52.830 --> 49:54.840
I have someone

49:56.200 --> 49:57.600
I can trust.

49:58.610 --> 50:00.260
You might not like her though.

50:00.560 --> 50:01.410
A guardian?

50:01.410 --> 50:04.720
Do you remember when I asked you about the black market?

50:06.180 --> 50:08.190
The kid is there.

50:08.350 --> 50:10.600
You saved her.

50:16.750 --> 50:17.770
Look at her.

50:17.770 --> 50:20.140
Why did you choose me for a guardian?

50:23.320 --> 50:26.370
I trust the ones who bring me luck.

50:27.840 --> 50:28.900
Okay.

50:28.900 --> 50:30.920
But I heard you're heading back to Korea.

50:30.920 --> 50:31.940
Yeah.

50:33.470 --> 50:35.190
Thanks for everything, Valentine.

50:36.510 --> 50:37.660
Good luck to you.

50:38.070 --> 50:39.530
Thank you.

50:41.130 --> 50:43.170
You need to listen to her.

50:43.880 --> 50:45.810
She's not as nice as me.

50:45.810 --> 50:46.990
And...

50:47.290 --> 50:50.560
Write me letters to the address that I gave you.

50:50.560 --> 50:51.760
No.

50:53.070 --> 50:54.450
Then just call me.

50:55.070 --> 50:56.270
No.

50:56.630 --> 50:58.100
How cheeky!

50:58.100 --> 50:58.940
Do you have to treat

50:58.940 --> 51:01.010
someone who's paying your tuition, like this?

51:01.010 --> 51:02.910
I guess teenagers are the same everywhere.

51:02.910 --> 51:03.860
Hey, girl!

51:05.060 --> 51:06.760
Be nice.

51:08.150 --> 51:08.830
Thank you for everything.

51:08.830 --> 51:10.780
I'll always be thankful. Stay safe.

51:14.180 --> 51:15.150
You're some girl,

51:15.150 --> 51:16.360
aren't you?

51:18.870 --> 51:21.250
I'll always wonder what you will be.

51:21.250 --> 51:22.330
So stay in touch.

51:22.330 --> 51:23.550
Just to let you know.

51:23.550 --> 51:25.470
By the way,

51:25.940 --> 51:28.390
I meant every word that I just said.

51:28.620 --> 51:29.680
I know.

51:56.140 --> 51:58.070
What do you want to do the most when you go back to Korea?

52:00.140 --> 52:02.830
I want to take a hot bath for a long time.

52:03.500 --> 52:04.510
What about you?

52:05.480 --> 52:06.900
I want to watch you do that.

52:11.130 --> 52:12.320
Let's watch a movie.

52:12.630 --> 52:13.740
We haven't been able to watch one.

52:14.990 --> 52:18.160
Why is it so hard to watch a movie with you?

52:19.510 --> 52:20.690
Okay.

52:20.690 --> 52:22.130
When we go to Korea,

52:22.130 --> 52:24.620
let's stay away from kidnapping and rescuing

52:24.620 --> 52:25.980
and let's do what other couples do.

52:26.770 --> 52:28.040
Let's watch a movie, eat dinner,

52:28.040 --> 52:30.260
have coffee and you'll walk me home.

52:30.260 --> 52:31.900
You'll take a hot bath.

52:35.120 --> 52:36.130
Stop right there.

52:37.810 --> 52:39.730
Go home. I'll be right behind you.

52:40.730 --> 52:42.530
Don't go to a hotel with Mr. Han.

52:43.110 --> 52:46.100
Don't flirt with Yoon Gi.

52:46.100 --> 52:47.800
I told you to stop.

52:47.800 --> 52:48.950
And this.

52:56.710 --> 52:59.350
Do you still have this?

53:01.390 --> 53:02.660
People believe that

53:02.660 --> 53:04.430
if you take a pebble from here,

53:05.120 --> 53:07.520
you'll come back for sure.

53:10.700 --> 53:12.240
Take it.

53:18.030 --> 53:19.710
Why don't you see if it's true?

53:20.780 --> 53:23.070
To see if you come back.

53:37.470 --> 53:39.070
Thank you for everything.

53:42.200 --> 53:43.550
You too.

54:15.510 --> 54:16.340
One, two, three, four!

54:16.340 --> 54:17.550
-There are
-There are

54:17.550 --> 54:19.190
-lots of
-lots of

54:19.190 --> 54:21.940
cool guys.

54:23.940 --> 54:26.010
You got up early.

54:26.390 --> 54:28.620
I didn't want to miss even a second.

54:29.150 --> 54:31.340
Bye bye, my pigeons!

54:34.140 --> 54:37.350
Huh? There's a guy we haven't seen before.

54:37.900 --> 54:38.540
Who is he?

54:38.540 --> 54:40.790
Right? In the right front?

54:41.300 --> 54:43.540
He doesn't fit in.

54:49.120 --> 54:50.220
Oh my!

55:01.730 --> 55:03.590
He hated them so much.

55:04.710 --> 55:06.440
I think he's doing it for you.

55:07.990 --> 55:10.490
Dr. Song is such a sweet guy.

55:13.970 --> 55:16.540
Can you two start dating?

55:17.250 --> 55:20.080
I have to go. I haven't finished packing yet.

55:21.550 --> 55:22.730
Oh my god!

55:23.400 --> 55:25.830
Was it something I wrong?

55:26.420 --> 55:27.790
You didn't say anything wrong.

55:28.210 --> 55:29.170
Ms. Ha is

55:29.170 --> 55:30.450
as sweet as Dr. Song.

55:31.120 --> 55:33.310
She's like the character from "Candy Candy."

55:33.310 --> 55:35.350
What are you talking about?

55:36.220 --> 55:37.670
You're too young to know.

55:44.240 --> 55:45.220
Let's go.

56:51.720 --> 56:53.810
One, two, three.

56:56.320 --> 56:57.210
Attention!

56:59.530 --> 57:00.510
Salute!

57:12.450 --> 57:13.800
Good morning, everyone!

57:13.800 --> 57:15.470
Good morning!

57:15.910 --> 57:18.320
It's too far to commute.

57:18.320 --> 57:19.460
I loved the fact that

57:19.460 --> 57:21.130
the medical zone was right in front of my tent.

57:21.410 --> 57:23.760
We enjoyed the pigeons every morning.

57:23.760 --> 57:25.250
Wait for me.

57:25.250 --> 57:26.020
Hello.

57:26.910 --> 57:30.510
Don't you feel like this is our first day of work?

57:30.510 --> 57:32.330
-I know.
-Right?

57:32.330 --> 57:36.010
Me too. It's so cold.

57:36.490 --> 57:38.060
Good morning.

57:38.940 --> 57:42.340
We're really back.

58:06.940 --> 58:10.640
-=Next Episode-=

58:10.640 --> 58:12.210
What the heck is going on?

58:12.210 --> 58:13.760
When did they get back?

58:16.170 --> 58:17.610
Oops! I remember here.

58:17.610 --> 58:19.950
Are you sending me  home now?

58:19.950 --> 58:21.490
Should I let you stay with me?

58:21.490 --> 58:25.700
We're guarding the conference room on the 17th floor.

58:25.700 --> 58:27.200
How can you do this?

58:27.200 --> 58:29.460
How can you let me find out like this?

58:29.460 --> 58:32.390
When I ran away, I was trying to make you realize...

58:32.390 --> 58:34.100
We're done.

58:34.520 --> 58:35.690
Who's the idiot to start a gun fight

58:35.690 --> 58:38.500
in the middle of Seoul in broad daylight?

58:38.500 --> 58:39.660
Gun fight! Gun fight!

58:39.660 --> 58:40.980
We need backup! We need backup!

58:41.370 --> 58:42.880
I love you, Yoon Myung Joo.

58:42.880 --> 58:44.990
I love you very much.
